Class PatternSizeDialog

  • java.lang.Object
    • metadata.PatternSizeDialog

  • public final class PatternSizeDialog
extends java.lang.Object
    Pattern size dialog allows the user to set the sizes of the initPattern in the PatternEditor class. It sets the width and height values to the PatternEditor instance trough the PatternEditorController's singelton object.

    • Method Detail

      • createAndInitPatternSizeDialog

        public void createAndInitPatternSizeDialog()
        Initiates a dialog that lets the user insert the pattern sizes for a new board. The dialog contains two fields, width and height, and a trigger button. Triggering chechAndSetSizes(widthTextField, heightTextField).
        See Also:
        (javafx.scene.control.TextField, javafx.scene.control.TextField)

      • checkAndSetSizes

        public void checkAndSetSizes(javafx.scene.control.TextField widthTextField,
                             javafx.scene.control.TextField heightTextField)
        Checks if the input sizes is set to legal values. Compared in a simple matcher. Throwing a NumberFormatException and displaying a alert box to the user if the values were invalid(of non digit characters), calling patternSizeDialog if catch was initiated. If it was not the sizes will follow the PatternEditorController instance, and will be as PatternEditor's width and height.
        Parameters:
        widthTextField - widthTextField a JavaFX Textfield.
        heightTextField - heightTextField a JavaFX Textfield.
